<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-03-26T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-03-26T03:00:00-05:00" n="57" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d57">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">393.11/1091: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Canton</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Jenkins</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Canton</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-03-26T16:00:00+08:00">March 26, 1930—4
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received March 26—3:34 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Referring to my telegram of March 25, 4 p.m. Local government has
                            informed me of receipt of telegram from Governor of Kiangsi stating
                            troops despatched to Kanchow and that latter city considered safe.
                            Department, Legation and Hankow informed.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Jenkins</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>